Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees.

Bring @Pearl Barley{½%cup} (1 cup for 4 servings; save the rest for another use), half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later), 3 cups water (5 cups for 4), and a big pinch of @salt{} to a boil in a small #pot{}. Once boiling, reduce to a simmer; cover and cook until tender, ~{30-32%minutes}.

Reserve ¼ cup barley cooking liquid (⅓ cup for 4), then drain and return to pot.

While barley cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @Button Mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!).

== Roasted Carrots ==

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon}. Season with half the @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Creamy Mushroom Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms in an even layer; season with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, undisturbed, until lightly browned on one side, ~{2-3%minutes}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Turn off heat. Transfer to a #cutting board{}; wash out pan.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with remaining Fry Seasoning, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for mushrooms over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If chicken begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium and cover.

Turn off heat. Transfer to a cutting board and tent with #foil{}. Wash out pan and let cool slightly.

While chicken cooks, whisk together @Cream Cheese{2%tablespoon}, half the @White Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings), half the @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2%unit}, remaining garlic powder, and reserved barley cooking liquid in a medium #bowl{}.

> It's OK if there are lumps—the cream cheese will melt when it cooks.

Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop mushrooms; stir into the cream cheese mixture.

Add cream cheese mixture to pan used for chicken and cook over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, until reduced and thickened, ~{1-3%minutes}. Remove from heat and stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Add a splash of warm water if sauce seems too thick.

== To Serve ==

Add @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1%unit} and remaining chicken stock concentrate to pot with barley; stir to combine.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide barley, chicken, and carrots between plates. Spoon mushroom sauce over chicken and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.